Limbo Dirt SHell v0.3.0-rc1 README
Summary:
ldsh is a lightweight shell, only around ~20KB in size once compiled.
It's quite basic, only running commands and outputting error codes, meaning it does not have any form of shell script support.
(To run shell scripts simply write bash ./foo.sh, or whatever shell you use)

Installation:
ldsh is built with the make build system, so simply follow the instructions of that.
Default installation directory is /usr/local/bin.
(run ./configure, then make, and then make install)

Built in commands:
While there aren't many, ldsh has a few built in commands, which may be useful to know.
echo: prints all arguments past arg0
exit: leaves the shell and either returns you to your previous shell, bash, zsh or fish, or if ldsh is your first shell, exits the terminal.
cd: changes directory, checks if arg1 is a real directory, then changes to it
ldsh --version: prints the version of ldsh.
help: prints this help menu inside of the shell
PS1: sets the ps1 variable inside of the shell.
PS1 usage: \grn, \red and \blu makes the next segment(s) green, red and blue respectively, (you can only have 5 colours). \u your USER, \w for the working directory \$ just prints $.

How often will this be updated?
Not really often if I'm being honest.
I am one person with practically 0 knowledge of C.
This is my greatest project yet, being only ~250 lines.
If you have suggestions to add, add them where normal bugs are reported.

